I need to compute the body hash properly. In `test-modules.js`, `verifyMessage` uses:
```
const normalized = normalizeBody(body);
const computedHash = simpleHash(normalized);
```

And the `simpleHash` function is internal to the IIFE. I need to either expose it or compute the hash in `sendTestMsg` using a local copy of the same algorithm.

Let me check what `simpleHash` does in `test-modules.js`:
```
function simpleHash(str) {
    let hash = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < str.length; i++) {
      const ch = str.charCodeAt(i);
      hash = (hash << 5) - hash + ch;
      hash |= 0;
    }
    return hash.toString(16);
  }
```

And `normalizeBody`:
```
function normalizeBody(body) {
    const keys = Object.keys(body).sort();
    const result = {};
    for (const k of keys) result[k] = body[k];
    return JSON.stringify(result);
}
```

I can add a `computeHash` helper in `sendTestMsg` that mirrors this logic.

